<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN270-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai, karantai; tuṟai, kaiyaṟunilai. kaḻāttalaiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN270">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>paṉmī ṉimaikku māka vicumpi</l>
<l>ṉiraṅku muraci ṉiṉañcāl yāṉai</l>
<l>nilantava vuruṭṭiya nēmi yōruñ</l>
<l>camaṅkaṇ kūṭit tāmvēṭ pavvē</l>
<l>naṟuvirai tuṟanta nāṟā naraittalaic</l>
<l>ciṟuvar tāyē pēriṟ peṇṭē</l>
<l>nōkō yāṉē nōkkumati nīyē</l>
<l>maṟappaṭai nuvalu marikkura ṟaṇṇumai</l>
<l>yiṉṉicai kēṭṭa tuṉṉaru maṟavar</l>
<l>veṉṟitaru vēṭkaiyar maṉṟaṅ koṇmār</l>
<l>pērama ruḻanta veruvaru paṟantalai</l>
<l>viḻunavi pāynta marattiṉ</l>
<l>vāḷmicaik kiṭanta vāṇmaiyōṉ tiṟattē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>They are desirous of joining the battle</l>
<l>of numerous elephants in troups, with sounding drums,</l>
<l>and of those with wheels that rolled much across the ground,</l>
<l>like the sky where many stars twinkle.</l>
<l>With unscented white heads that had given up fragrant substances,</l>
<l>oh mothers of children, oh women of great houses,</l>
<l>I ache. Look</l>
<l>at him who had manliness who [now] lies on [his] sword,</l>
<l>like a tree that was attacked by an excellent axe,</l>
<l>in the frightening waste land that bore a great battle</l>
<l>when bold warriors difficult to approach who had heard the sweet sound</l>
<l>of the Taṇṇumai drum with a cutting voice that calls [together] the bold army,</l>
<l>so that those desirous of victory would take the village common.   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
